# Amla Licensing

Amla-owned code in this package is available under either of these license
choices:

- GNU Affero General Public License v3.0 or later (`AGPL-3.0-or-later`)
- Business Source License 1.1 (`BUSL-1.1`), changing to the MIT License three
  years after the first public distribution of each specific version

You may use Amla-owned code under either license choice. Commercial licenses
are available under a separate written agreement with Amla.

The full license texts and BUSL parameters are in:

- `LICENSES/AGPL-3.0-or-later.txt`
- `LICENSES/BUSL-1.1.txt`

When you run `kalahari prepare`, the prepared microVM rootfs and kernel embed
material under additional licenses (notably Linux kernel sources under
`GPL-2.0-only`). Compliance notices for those components ship with the
prepared image artifacts, not with this npm package.
